1. How to set justify property in the paragraph elements?
Ans:
Use the text-align property with the value justify:

css:
p {
  text-align: justify;
}
This will make the text in all <p> elements align evenly on both left and right sides.


2. How to add shadow to text?
Use the text-shadow property:

css:
h1 {
  text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px gray;
}
Format: text-shadow: horizontal-offset vertical-offset blur-radius color;

3. How to specify all the font properties in one declaration?
Use the font shorthand property:


css:

p {
  font: italic small-caps bold 16px/1.5 Arial, sans-serif;
}
Format: font: [style] [variant] [weight] [size]/[line-height] [family];

Example (simpler):

css:
p {
  font: 16px Arial, sans-serif;
}
Let me know if you'd like examples applied in an HTML page.